learning_outcomes.en:
Upon successful completion of this course, students will: 
Have obtained a detailed knowledge of the main factors that shape the foreign policy formation process, allowing them to apply these throughout their MA studies; 
Have obtained a comprehensive knowledge of the main models proposed to account for decision-making dynamics in the foreign policy formation process, allowing them to apply these throughout their MA studies; 
Have obtained a detailed understanding of the physiological, cognitive and rational-choice approaches regularly applied in the Foreign Policy Analysis (FPA) literature; 
Have gained detailed insights into the linkages between FPA and International Relations Theory;  
Have learned to practically apply models explaining foreign policy decision-making to "real-world" events through a group presentation; 
Have furthered their skills in researching and writing policy memorandums and argumentative scholarly essays.

learning_outcomes.et:
Pärast edukat kursuse lõpetamist, üliõpilased:
- on saanud põhjalikud teadmised peamistest teguritest, mis kujundavad välispoliitika muutuseid; 
- on saanud põhjalikud teadmised erinevatest lähenemisviisidest, mida kohaldatakse välispoliitikat kajastatavates väljaannetes; 
- on saanud põhjalikud teadmised välispoliitika ja rahvusvaheliste suhete teooria suhtest;
- on õppinud rakendama praktiliselt erinevaid mudelid, mida kasutatakse välispoliitika otsustusprotsessides;
- on täiendanud uurimustööde ja esseede kirjutamise oskuseid.
